U.S. Customs and Border ProtectionThey crossed the border as families.
Under a new Trump administration policy, families caught crossing the border illegally were split up, parents and children separated and their cases swallowed up by different federal agencies, each its own bureaucratic maze.
The government assigns every undocumented immigrant an “alien number,” but parents and children may not know each other’s or even their own.
Detention centers holding parents have posted flyers asking, “Have You Been Separated From Your Child(ren)?” in both English and Spanish.
“I can’t really imagine any religious person that would support a policy of separating children from their families.